{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Xy3rVEGQrFByBkRm6JevKK","type":"tool_result","content":"commit 452a433cbff6218786740a62be99d8f0f54eacdd\nAuthor: Ian McLaughlin <ian.mclaughlin@prizeout.com>\nDate:   Mon May 18 23:21:05 2026 -0400\n\n    coro: pure-Lua resume/yield (Phase E-2, slice 02b)\n    \n    Wire coroutine.resume / coroutine.yield to do_::lua_resume / lua_yieldk\n    for pure Lua coroutines. LuaError::Yield unwinds Rust frames back to the\n    lua_resume boundary; the existing call_no_yield path on pcall already\n    rejects yields with the C-Lua-equivalent error.\n    \n    - ThreadRegistryEntry::state: GcRef<LuaState> -> Rc<RefCell<LuaState>>\n      so resume can borrow the child mutably while parent is in scope.\n    - aux_resume implements the full xmove / lua_resume / xmove sequence:\n      copies args from parent to child, swaps current_thread_id to the\n      child for the duration of the call, then moves results back.\n    - co_wrap now creates a real coroutine and captures it as upvalue 1;\n      aux_wrap forwards calls through aux_resume and raises errors.\n    - Removed wrap_iter_state and yield_buffers fields plus the\n      push/pop/has/yield_buffer_push_batch helpers — the generator-emulation\n      hack is fully replaced by real resume/yield.\n    - co_yield no longer checks the buffer; it always calls lua_yieldk.\n    \n    Acceptance test passes (resume returning values, yield/resume exchange,\n    wrap-raises-errors). coroutine.lua still fails at line 56 due to a\n    pre-existing cross-thread upvalue bug (open upvalues store thread_id\n    but upvalue_get reads from the current thread's stack) — out of scope\n    for this slice per spec.\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e41a7a40-0733-4140-a39a-79fe7f5c39df","uuid":"726e927c-a7a2-4cd9-8fa2-6376a54a33f3","timestamp":"2026-05-19T04:07:53.275Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"commit 452a433cbff6218786740a62be99d8f0f54eacdd\nAuthor: Ian McLaughlin <ian.mclaughlin@prizeout.com>\nDate:   Mon May 18 23:21:05 2026 -0400\n\n    coro: pure-Lua resume/yield (Phase E-2, slice 02b)\n    \n    Wire coroutine.resume / coroutine.yield to do_::lua_resume / lua_yieldk\n    for pure Lua coroutines. LuaError::Yield unwinds Rust frames back to the\n    lua_resume boundary; the existing call_no_yield path on pcall already\n    rejects yields with the C-Lua-equivalent error.\n    \n    - ThreadRegistryEntry::state: GcRef<LuaState> -> Rc<RefCell<LuaState>>\n      so resume can borrow the child mutably while parent is in scope.\n    - aux_resume implements the full xmove / lua_resume / xmove sequence:\n      copies args from parent to child, swaps current_thread_id to the\n      child for the duration of the call, then moves results back.\n    - co_wrap now creates a real coroutine and captures it as upvalue 1;\n      aux_wrap forwards calls through aux_resume and raises errors.\n    - Removed wrap_iter_state and yield_buffers fields plus the\n      push/pop/has/yield_buffer_push_batch helpers — the generator-emulation\n      hack is fully replaced by real resume/yield.\n    - co_yield no longer checks the buffer; it always calls lua_yieldk.\n    \n    Acceptance test passes (resume returning values, yield/resume exchange,\n    wrap-raises-errors). coroutine.lua still fails at line 56 due to a\n    pre-existing cross-thread upvalue bug (open upvalues store thread_id\n    but upvalue_get reads from the current thread's stack) — out of scope\n    for this slice per spec.\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
