{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Gevyuh9JyBhULEC9BjMwEU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the \"DBG concat\" debug message is from the lua-rs runtime itself (not a debug print I added). But it's not found in the crates directory. Let me search more broadly.\n\nAlso, I see that commit 452a433 completely replaced the wrap/yield mechanism. The old \"generator-emulation hack\" was replaced with real resume/yield. This is likely what broke things.\n\nThe coroutine.wrap creates a real coroutine now, and `for s in coroutine.wrap(...)` iterates by calling the wrapped function. \n\nWhen `gen` yields `c` (a string), the wrapped function returns the string. The for loop assigns `s = c`.\n\n\nBut the error shows `s` is actually a Table—specifically the local `x = {\"=\", \"[\", \"]\", \"\\n\"}` from the outer scope. This suggests coroutine.wrap might be returning the iterator's internal state instead of the yielded value, or the xmove operation is transferring the wrong values between coroutines. I need to check the coro_lib.rs implementation to see what's actually happening.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4584,"cache_read_input_tokens":37938,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4584},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e41a7a40-0733-4140-a39a-79fe7f5c39df","uuid":"34eb1591-66bc-4a0f-9b39-aa1800356f63","request_id":"req_011CbBGawFzhG4pgjA794iss"}
