{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01M15baa7MFDNHfdKmobGWdb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue. In `aux_resume`, let me trace through what happens when `gen` yields:\n\n1. `gen(\"\", 4)` is called from the body function of the coroutine\n2. Inside gen, when n > 0, it iterates: `for _, a in pairs(x) do gen(c..a, n-1) end`\n3. When n==0, it calls `coroutine.yield(c)` where `c` is a string\n\nWhen `coroutine.yield(c)` is called with 1 argument, `lua_yieldk` is called. \n\nThis unwinds the Rust call frames and returns to `lua_resume`. After that returns, I'm extracting the yielded values from the coroutine's stack by calculating the range based on the stack top and result count, then collecting them into a vector.\n\nNow I need to trace through `lua_yieldk` and `lua_resume` to understand what `nres` actually represents when a yield happens.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8534,"cache_read_input_tokens":42957,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":8534},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e41a7a40-0733-4140-a39a-79fe7f5c39df","uuid":"8959d34c-9dd1-4341-a752-89c3a4b1ca81","request_id":"req_011CbBGbkg2twNji4doCUJU8"}
